----INTRODUCTION TO API----

What is an API?
 https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=s7wmiS2mSXY

HTTP protocol and request methods
1. GET <- minta data dari server, data sudah ada dalam server
2. PUT <- mengganti data atau membuat data baru bila data blm ada
3. POST <- membuat data baru 
   #direkomendasikan PUT buat update POST buat baru
4. DELETE <- menghapus data atau resources

Endpoints <- access points to data or computing resources hosted on a server and they take the form of an HTTP URI. Endpoints are added to an API's base URL (e.g. http://example.com) to create a path to a specific resource or container of resources.

RESTful API <- APIs that utilize the HTTP protocol, request methods, and endpoints
 
RESful API bisa minta ini kalu request :
 + Headers: parameters that detail the HTTP request itself.
 + Body: data that a client wants to send to a server.
keduanya dalam bentuk JSON atau XML

API Data Formats (JSON)
 Format JSON = {"" : "" , "" : ""}

Authentication and Authorization
 + Authentication identifies who you are.
 + Authorization determines what you can do.

There are three types of authentication/authorization services that Google APIs use.
1. API Keys <- secret tokens that usually come in the form of an encrypted string.
2. OAuth <- tokens are similar to API keys in their format, but they are more secure and can be linked to user accounts or identities. 
3. service account <- special type of Google account that belongs to your application or a virtual machine (VM) instead of to an individual end user.

